	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK I have a 10th level high elf cleric.<br>I love my cleric but I have noticed that soloing is becoming more and more difficult for me (even soloing blues in steamfront mountains).  I made a mistake a character creation and I don't know if I should be worried about it.  As you know HEs get the highest starting wiz.  I did NOT add any pts to wiz but instead added most pts to strength (with like 5 to charisma I think).  I have 4 pieces of jewelry from a friend at +2 wiz a piece giving me 113 wisdom.  My question is am I in trouble?  I checked out the wisdom to mana chart at EQ Cleric and at level 30 with 115 base wisdom and the +8 in modifiers I would have 60 more mana than I do with 105 wiz and the modifiers.  Is this a big deal?  I've heard there are alot of things that can increase your stats considerably.  Please I need some advice from an experienced cleric before I put a great deal more time into this character.  Should I recreate?<br>I put most of my points into strength because HEs have the lowest strength (start at 65) and I thought I needed it for soloing since Clerics don't have real strong DD spells and can't do the damage in melee that a tank can.  Please help<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
