<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9735725896402></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9735725896402><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=7&mid=9735725896402>RE: A question on wisdom (need quick response plz!)</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 6th 11:49 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It all comes down to you in the end<br><br>            If you die, or let half your party die, that 200 wisdom isnt going to help you ( other than rezz's =p).  Knowing when, how, and who to heal is more important than 200 wisdom same goes for knowing when to med. in battle.  Granted the 200 wisdom can help ALOT =p, hehe, it still is how you use it, I play a Human Cleric ::gasp:: and with a base of 95 wisdom people think im nuts that I even bother to play em,  But to put it plainly im good =p, I know when, who, and how to heal/med.  How to time the first heal so you can pull 1 or 2 mobs off the tanks in a huge melee and park them.  Or time your first heal as not to aggro anything. I find at 40th lvl with 164 wisdom I do just fine in Lguk or Sol B with a group my lvl, on average I can keep at least halfmana after each battle when pulling steady, and if the $#% hits the fan I still have that half mana( 2.5 bubs) to burn.  As far as soloing goes, its possible but the down time is killer and your better off in a group, unless your soloing a single spawn with a nice spawn time, but then you'd more the likely get more exp with a group.  Specs are nice though =p<br>Humans rock,  I love being average =p  89, 88, 87, 88, 164, 87, 80<br><br><br>Merulus M'Hael<br>Fennin Ro Sever<br><br>" Shepards  we shall be, for thee my lord, for thee<br>   Power haft decended forth from thine hand, so that our feet my swiftly carry out thine command<br>   And we shall open a River unto thee<br>   And teeming with shadow'd soul's shall it ever be"<br><br>what! no spellcheck? ::mutters and walks away::<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
