	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, sorry to break it to you (which is so ironic considering everyone else has said this), but a Cleric is not a melee class. You CAN solo -the undead. I have a Gnomish Cleric on Lanys T'vyl that will be a solo cleric. The reason? Low wisdom. His base WIS is 100, and he will be chronically short on mana.<br><br>If you really want a solo cleric, I'd suggest a dwarf, as they have high STR, STA, and AGI.<br><br>As for where to put your points, it depends on your style of play. I would generally recommend getting your STR to 75 or 85, and dumping the rest into WIS. If you're going to solo, put points into AGI so you won't get hit as often. Don't worry about INT or CHA.<br><br>Good luck!<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
