	   <tr><td colspan=2>My opinion is that it all depends on how you want to play your character.  I originally thought I did a boo-boo by not putting any into wis.  I put 10 each into dex and agi, and 5 each into str and sta.  Granted, I may not have as much mana as a cleric of my level that maxed their wis, but I think having 150 wis (which comes to 1035 mana with my +mana eq) isn't bad for a level 30.  My advantage is that I get hit a LOT less when monsters agro me after a heal.  Many a person I have grouped with has told me this.  When I get hit less, there's that much better chance that I can get that extra heal on myself (if the only healer), or any other effective spell at the time.  I also don't know if there's any truth to this, but dex also might help with how often specialization works are higher levels (same reasoning behind dex raising the chance of a weapon proc).  It all just depends on what you want to do with your cleric.<br><br>Yamdari, 30 Cleric, among others :)<br>Bertoxxolous<br><br>P.S.  If you plan on soloing, be a dwarf...the extra str and sta come in real handy.  Also, invest in ruby jewelry (str and wis...can't beat it)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
